```
import re

def palindrome_of_length_n(string):
    string = string.lower()
    pattern = r'[a-z]{16}'
    palindromes = re.findall(pattern, string)
    return set(palindromes)
```
Note: The given code finds palindromes of length 16 by using regular expressions. It converts the given string to lowercase and uses the regular expression pattern '[a-z]{16}' to search for substrings of length 16 consisting of only English letters. It returns a set containing all the found palindromes.
